Rating: 4
I made ths recipe many years ago and lost track of it until today. I found it to be one of the best chicken recipes I'd ever tasted II am surprised by seeing the polar opposite remarks on here but it just goes to show how different our tastes all are). I love the marinade because the buttermilk breaks down the texture into a silky product. I love the cornmeal crust idea and the moistness of the chicken was delicious. I am making this again tonight!

Rating: 4
A friend of mine told me this was a favorite recipe of hers from long ago. I recently made it for my family and it was outstanding. The layers of flavor and texture couldn't be better. It didn't get soggy on the bottom, crispy all the way around. It was a little time consuming, but could be prepared ahead. My husband and "picky" teenage children loved it. I can't wait to make it again. Well worth the effort!

Rating: 3
This has been a staple in my house for years. I think the important flavorings are the cayenne, the lemon zest and the shallots in the marinade. I never have buttermilk, so I use milk soured with vinegar. This is very good as a hot dish, but doesn't travel well to a picnic in my opinion.

