Rating: 3
This recipe was excellent with a small variation. I used 3 pounds of boneless, skinless chicken breasts and cut them into thirds. I also marinated the chicken overnight. I found it extremely flavorful and tender, and the coating was thick, crisp and delicious. This was the second time I made it; I was also impressed the first time, however when eaten cold later the skin was rubbery and unappealing, which was why I decided to try it skinless. I definitely recommend this. It would be a wonderful picnic dish.

Rating: 1
With all the preparation and spices, I would have expected this to be much more flavorful. I am not a fried chicken fan anyway, so perhaps I'm prejudiced. There are better chicken dishes in these pages, that's for sure.